3:
You people of the city of Heshbon, wail,\q2 because the city of Ai will be destroyed.
\q1 You women in the city of Rabbah, weep;
\q2 put on rough clothing to show you are mourning;
\q1 run back and forth in confusion inside the city walls,
\q2 because your god Molech, along with its priests and officials, will be taken away in exile.
\q1

31:
But I say to Nebuchadnezzar,\q1 'Go up and attack that nation whose people feel secure;
\q2 they do not have allies who will help them and do not have walls with gates that have bars in them.


\q1

33:
Hazor will become a place where jackals live,\q2 and it will be deserted forever.
\q1 No one will live there again;
\q2 no people will settle there. '"
